review_blob: Thanks to Chuck for saving a burning orphanage, curing cancer, and standing in line to get this beer!  The aroma is very pleasant and chocolatey.  It has a nice, pitch black color, thick body, and a nice creamy brown head.  The flavor is excellent, roasty and a definite strength, but nothing too poweful to detract from the enjoyment of the beer.  It has an excellent body and texture, thick and viscous.  Overall, this is a groin-grabbingly excellent beer.

Thanks Chuck for the sample!  Has a nice dark amber body and foamy white head.  Nice malty aroma.  Excellent flavor, plenty of hops and spices.  Has a good body and texture, and good, lively carbonation.  Overall, very good.  This makes for an excellent sesquicentennial rating.

Thanks Matt for the sample!  Has a nice malty and carmel aroma.  Pours a murky red-brown, with a wisp of white head.  Flavor is decent, somewhat bitter, somewhat acidic.  Body is kind of light, cabonation OK.  Overall, its decent, but not spectacular.

Thanks to Chuck for the sample!  Has a pretty nice coffee aroma, with a little alcohol noticable.  Black body with a thin beige head.  Flavor is nice, bitter, coffe-flavored.  Decent body and texture, and lively carbonation.  Overall, this is a good beer.
beer_name: Full Sail Black Gold Imperial Stout Bourbon Barrel Aged

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Thanks to Dave for the sample!  Has a decent, kind of strong malty aroma.  Deep black body, with a nice frothy tan head.  Flavor is kind of bland, bitter and slightly acidic, but not much else.  Decent body and texture, and lively carbonation.  Overall, its OK, but not something Im a fan of.

Thanks to Chuck for the sample!  Has a murky brown body, with a thin white head, and some sediment on the bottom.  Noticable alcohol aomra to it.  Flavor is pretty good, once again, noticable on the alcohol.  Body and texture are decent, with decent carbonation.  Overall, its nice, but I cant rate is highly are others would.

Has a very mild, smoky aroma to it.  Its hard to pickup, but its there.  Otherwise, really no other aroma to pick up on.  Has a pretty good dark amber body, some bubbling, and a thing white head.  Like the aroma, it has a smoky flavor to it, with no other noticable flavors.  Its more like a smoked ale than a barley wine... Decent body and lively carbonation.  Overall, its pretty good.

Massive map props to Chuck for a sample!  Has a nice deep violet body, with a beige head.  Has a very good chocolate/raspberry aroma to it.  Has a very good flavor, definite chocolate and caramel to it,  and no unpleasant alcohol flavor for something with a higher alcohol content.  Good body and the right amount of carbonation.  Overall, very, very good.

Thanks to Chuck for the sample!  Has a nice cloudy light brown body, with a VERY LARGE foamy white head (I poured it after someone else had opened and taken a sample, and there was a nice "column of foam" coming out of the bottle, like a snake firefwork).  Has a nice subdued aroma, slightly spicy and hoppy.  Flavor is kind of watered down, but has a noticable yeast and carmel flavor to it.  Body is OK.  Overall, its an interesting beer, but I dont think I would try it again.

Has a pretty good mild malt aroma to it.  Decent hazy brown body with a white, foamy head.  Flavor isnt too good, slightly malty, but rather non-pleasing.  Light body, with decent carbonation.  Overall, this isnt too good.

Has a nice, slightly subdued malty aroma to it.  Nice brown amber body, some bubbles present, with a beige head.  Flavor is not bad, kind of noticable on the alcohol and bitter, although it feels a bit off (sort of like ice cubes from a tap faucet that have been in the freezer a while).  Has a good body and carbonation.  Overall, it is pretty enjoyable.

Thanks Blake for the sample!  Has an OK hoppy, piney aroma.  Hazy orange body, with a thin white head.  Flavor is rather blah, slightly bitter, but theres nothing really flavorful that makes it stand out.  Decent body and carbonation.  Overall, its drinkable, but not too enjoyable.

Has a decent cloudy amber body, with little head.  Has a nice hoppy aroma to it.  Flavor is decent, slightly orange flavor, although it seems kind of light and empty.  Body likewise is kind of light, with the right amount of carbonation.  Overall, its decent, but not spectactular.

Has a good deep black-red body to it, with a foamy beige head.  Has a bit of a wooden aroma to it (likely from the Oak barrels its aged in).  Likewise, the flavor is noticably woody, but with noticable cherry flavor as well.  Try to think of it as having a cherry flavored popsicle, except the cherry flavor is real.  However, its kind of hard for me to get past the wooden flavor to it.  It has a decent body, and little carbonation to it.  Overall, its pretty good, but I cant rate it as highly as others have.
beer_name: New Glarus Thumbprint Series Cherry Stout

review_blob: Has a very pleasant mild cherry aroma.  Pours with a hazy reddish-brown body, and athin, fizzy head.  Excellent flavor, obviously cherry.  Its just right, not too strong, and not too mild.  Body is kind of light, but with the right amount of carbonation.  Overall, I can see why this is rated so highly.  Its very good.

Thanks to Jason for getting this added!  This has a wonderful aroma, rich in malts and carmel.  It pours with a brown body, and a thin beige head.  The flavor is quite pleasant, malty and bitter, and a little strong.  It has a decent body and texture and carbonation.  Overall, this was quite good.

Thanks to Dave for the sample!  Has a decent aroma, piney and citrusy.  Nice cloudy golden brown body and a thin white head.  Flavor is mild, slighty hoppy and spicy.  Decent body and carbonation.  Overall, this is pretty nice.
beer_name: Heavyweight Saison de la Soeur Spicy

review_blob: Has a wonderful hoppy aroma.  Nice darker amber body and white head.  Flavor is pretty nice, somewhat hoppy, but seems to have a bit of grapefruit - pretty interesting.  Has a decent body and carbonation.  Overall, this is quite good and enjoyable.

Thanks to Blake for the sample!  Has a nice roasty and malty aroma.  Nice dark body, with a large brown head took a few minutes to settle down.  An odd, but overall pleasing flavor, fruity and sour.  Has a decent body and carbonation.  Overall, pretty good.

Thanks to Dave for the sample!  Has a nice spicy, citrusy aroma to it.  Has a cloudy brown body and a thick white head that takes a few minutes to dissapate.  Flavor is nice, hoppy and spicy, but a little subdued.  Decent body, but a little strong on the carbonation.  Overall, pretty good.
beer_name: Heavyweight Saison de la Soeur Hoppy

review_blob: Thanks to Jason for the sample!  Has a pleasant malty, carmel aroma.  Decent cloudy brown body with a tan head.  Nice flavor, its a mix of malts and fruits.  Has a good body, although the carbonation is a little overpowering.  Overall, however, this is pretty pleasing.

Has a pleasant malty aroma.  Nice deep brown body with a thin tan head.  Flavor is kind of weak, slightly roasty, but not much to pick up on.  Body and texture is kind of light.  Overall, theres not much character to this, and as a result, I dont really care for it.

Has a mild malty, corn aroma to it.  Yellow body, some bubbled, with a foamy white head.  Flavor is thin, slightly hoppy, but generally not distinct.  Has a thin body, such that you notice the carbonation more.  Overall, this is rather blah.

Has a decent malty, fruity aroma to it.  Has a deep brown amber color, with a thin tan head.  Flavor is pretty good, fruity, noticable alcohol flavor as well.  Has a decent body and texture, with little carbonation.  Overall, this is pretty good.  Too bad its retired now...
Pleasant mild hoppy aroma to it.  Has a nice dark brown body with a tan head.  Pleasing flavor, bitter and hoppy.  Nice body and texture and carbonation.  Overall, this is quite good.
beer_name: Bear Republic Hop Rod Rye Ale

review_blob: Thanks Chuck for the freebie.  Has a pleasant, fragrant hoppy aroma to it.  Has a nice amber body and foamy white head.  Flavor is wonderful, nice and quite hoppy.  Decent body and texture, and decent carbonation.  Overall, this is a quit enjoyable beer.

Thanks Blake for the sample.  Has a medium malty aroma.  Nice cloudy amber body and white head.  Pleasant, slightly bitter flavor, also slightly sweet.  Nice body and texture.  Overall, this is pretty good.
beer_name: Marin Star Brew Triple Wheat Ale

review_blob: Has a subtle malty aroma to it.  Nice copper amber color with a thin white head.  Slightly bitter flavor, but seems kind of light.  OK body and texture and carbonation.  Overall, its a decent beer.
Thanks Blake for the sample.  Has an icky hoppy aroma to it.  Pale yellow body with a thin white head.  Flavor is largely non-existant.  Light body with a little carbonation.  Not good at all.
Thanks to Chuck for the sample.  Has a rather pleasant malty and citrusy aroma.  Nice darker amber color with a foamy tan head.  Nice malty flavor.  Has a good body.  Overall, this is pretty good.

Much thanks to Dave for the freebie!  Has a decent malty and fruity aroma.  Nice hazy brown body, with a little beige head.  Flavor is quite pleasant, slightly sour and fruity.  Good body and carbonation.  Overall, I found this quite enjoyable.

Thanks to Blake for the sample.  Nice smoky aroma, definitely like sniffing from a salmon feast.  Decent dark body and a brown head.  Decent mild roasty aroma, although it seems a little thin for body.  Overall, its kind of nice.

Thanks Chuck for the sample.  Has a pleasant roasty aroma to it.  Deep black color with a tan head.  Pretty weak flavor, very slightly bitter.  Also thin body and texture.  Maybe we got a bad bottle, because this seems like XX instead of XXXXX.

Has an odd aroma, kind of musty and antiseptic at the same time (it actually reminds me of the preservatives they use for pigs that you dissect in high school).  Decent dark amber color with a white head.  Quite sweet, but not as much as the Calvados.  OK body with decent cabonation.  The taste is kind of nice, but the aroma puts me off.

Thanks for Chuck for the sample.  Has a strong malty aroma.  Slightly cloudy dark amber color with a foamy white head.  Very sweet, it masks the stronger alcohol content.  Good body and decent carbonation.  Overall, its not bad.

Has a nice hazy golden body with a foamy white head.  Nice malty aroma.  Pretty good malty flavor, not too weak or too strong.  Kind of a fuller body anf texture, but little carbonation.  Overall, its pretty nice, and would probably go well with a bowl of Lucky Charms.

Deep dark black body, from which no light can escape (like sating into my soul).  Wonderful mild chocolately aroma.  Has an excellent roasty and sweet chocolate flavor.  Also has a good body and carbonation.  Overall, this is very good,  A real treat.
beer_name: Tyranena BGW Whos Your Daddy? Bourbon Barrel-Aged Imperial Porter

review_blob: Slighty hoppy aroma, but very faint.  Pale orange color with a thin white head.  Slightly bitter, but otherwise nothing special.  OK body and carbonation.  Overall, its OK, but nothing spectacular.

Tried the 1994.  Strong aroma, oddly like soy sauce.  Pours deep black and thick, like the dark water in The Pirates of Dark Water, with no head.  Odd chocolatey-raisin-soy sauce flavor, its at least not offensive for having 18% alcohol.  Extremely thick, almost like syrup.  Overall, this is very odd.

Thanks to Chuck for the sample.  Has a nice roasty malt aroma.  Very dark, pours almost like motor oil.  Has a nice roasty flavor, quite enjoyable.  Thick body, with good carbonation.  Overall, this is quite good.

Has a pretty nice oatmeal and chocolate aroma.  Nice black color with a little brown head.  Has a coffee flavor, slightly bitter, although it seems a little off somehow.  Nice body and carbonation.    Overall, its OK, but nothing I would seek out in the future.

Has a nice, fragrant sour aroma, like wine.  Pretty nice dark brown color, sort of like a cloudy cola, with a bit of head that takes a while to dissapate.  Flavor is nice, obviously very sour, vinegary.  Has a pretty nice body and texture, and decent carbonation.  Overall, a very pleasant surprise.
Has a pretty nice amber body, slightly hazy, witha frothy white head.  So-so aroma.  Flavor is not bad, slighty bitter.  Pretty good body, little carbonation.  Overall, its not bad.

Has a nice orange amber color, with little head.  Pleasant mild hoppy aroma to it.  Flavor is excellent, nice and hoppy and a little bitter.  Pretty good body, light on the carbonation.  Overall, this is good.

Has a decent malty aroma.  Murky dark brown color, with no head to speak of.  Flavor is kind of fruity, but not definite.  Kind of a light body and not much carbonation.  Overall, this is not my cup of tea (or beer).

Has a hazy amber color with a very thin white head.  Faint hoppy aroma, but almost non-existant.  Flavor is fairly pleasant, hoppy and a little spicy.  Kind of a light body, but good carbonation.  Overall, its OK, but nothing special.

Has a faint aroma, I can detect some malts and chocolate, but nothing noticable and pleasing.  Has a pretty nice deep dark brown color, with a thin tan head.  Pretty nice chocolate and nut flavor to it.  Decent body and texture, although the carbonation is a little too lively for me. Overall, this is pretty nice, and I would have it again.

Has a decent roasty aroma to it.  Deep black color, a little carbonation present, and a thin tan head.  Has a bitter flavor, but nothing really taste to it.  OK body, but the carbonation is kind of overpowering.  Overall, its palatable, but I dont think I would try it again.

Has a tart aroma to it, its kind of odd, but not bad.  Has a murky, muddy color with no head, has small, but definite sediment in it.  Taste is kind of strong in the alcohol department, but is definitely something that I can handle, is also kind of sweet.  Decent body and texture and carbonation.  Overall, its not too shabby.
